-- Bundesbank's Weber Backed by Kiel Institute for ECB Job, Handelsblatt Says
-- Andreas Cremer
-- 2010-06-22T04:56:41Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-22/bundesbank-s-weber-backed-by-kiel-institute-for-ecb-job-handelsblatt-says.html

          
          
             Axel Weber , the head of Germany’s
Bundesbank, would make a “fantastic president” of the European
Central Bank,  Handelsblatt  cited a senior economist as saying.  
 Dennis Snower , who heads the Kiel-based IfW institute of
world economics said Weber meets “all preconditions” for the
top ECB job, the newspaper reported.  
 To contact the reporters on this story:
